# Report: Why Are Staff Leaving Higher Education?

## Introduction

Staff turnover in higher education institutions (HEIs) has become a significant concern, impacting organizational stability, financial resources, and educational quality. This report provides a comprehensive analysis of the reasons why staff are leaving higher education, drawing on recent and relevant research. It synthesizes empirical findings, explores demographic and workload factors, and examines the exacerbating impact of the COVID-19 pandemic. The report aims to present an objective and in-depth understanding of the multifaceted causes of turnover in higher education, supported by quantitative data and scholarly insights.

## Financial Factors

### Compensation and Pay Disparities

One of the primary drivers of staff turnover in higher education is low compensation or limited salary increases. Employees often consider leaving when their pay is not competitive or when they perceive inequities in raises relative to their peers within the institution ([Figueroa, 2015](https://www.researchgate.net/publication/281269358_The_Influences_Impacting_Staff_Turnover_in_Higher_Education)). Budgetary constraints frequently limit the ability of HEIs to offer regular or substantial pay raises, which fuels dissatisfaction and turnover intentions ([Banks, 2019](https://www.researchgate.net/publication/335546543_The_Influences_Impacting_Staff_Turnover_in_Higher_Education)).

Financial costs of turnover are substantial. For example, some universities incur over $60 million annually due to lost work time, hiring and training expenses, and loss of institutional knowledge ([Figueroa, 2015](https://www.researchgate.net/publication/281269358_The_Influences_Impacting_Staff_Turnover_in_Higher_Education)). The average cost of onboarding a new staff member is approximately 25% of the salary of the departing employee, and filling a vacancy takes an average of 17.2 days nationally ([Silva & Toledo, 2009](https://www.researchgate.net/publication/281269358_The_Influences_Impacting_Staff_Turnover_in_Higher_Education)).

